Set-valued Probability Measures.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The simplest such set is the set 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathscr{L}_{2}=\left\{ \imposs,\poss\right\} $
\end_inset

 together with the operation 
\begin_inset Formula $\vee$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $x\vee y=\imposs$
\end_inset

